                       "message":  "PLAYMENU-DYNAMIC-ENABLE: grey out invalid Play-menu items per live PlayState\n\nFirst \"deepen the menu bar\" beat beyond static breadth: the Play menu items\n(Play/Pause/Stop/Step) now grey out (disabled-but-visible) when the current\nPlayState makes the transition a no-op, instead of being always-clickable with a\nbenign-swallowed no-op. Establishes a live \"menu state\" channel from editor-shell\nto the host, authority-clean (the PlayState state machine stays the sole owner of\ntransition validity).\n\neditor-shell (play_state.rs):\n- PlayState::can_play/can_pause/can_stop/can_step, derived from the canonical\n  state (can_play=!Playing; can_pause/can_stop=is_pie_active; can_step=Paused).\n- Consistency test pinning each can_* to whether the real transition succeeds, so\n  enablement can\u0027t drift from play()/pause()/stop()/step().\n\neditor-state (menu_state_snapshot.rs, new):\n- MenuStateSnapshot { play_can_start/pause/stop/step } — a read-only observation\n  aggregator (sibling to SaveStatusSnapshot, NOT a 6th coordination category, so\n  editor-state-ownership stays green) + all_enabled() for the host\u0027s pre-publish\n  fallback.\n\neditor-egui-host:\n- MenuStateHandoff = Handoff\u003cMenuStateSnapshot\u003e (latest-only, mirrors\n  SaveStatusHandoff); host owns the Arc + exposes it; render acquires the snapshot\n  and add_enabled()s each Play item via play_item_enabled (routes booleans only —\n  no validity rule re-encoded in the host).\n\neditor-shell (mod.rs + render_path.rs):\n- menu_state_handoff field (cloned from the host in init_render_state) +\n  EditorShell::menu_state_snapshot() (pure read from PlayState::can_*); published\n  each frame beside save_status.\n\nTests: can_*\u003c-\u003etransition consistency; menu_state_snapshot tracks Editing/Playing/\nPaused; play_item_enabled 1:1 routing. 9 files, 0 Cargo.toml. File/Edit/View menus\nstay unconditionally enabled (Play-only beat).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
