                       "message":  "PLAYMENU-DYNAMIC-ENABLE: widen handoff count/listing prose for the 3rd handoff\n\nCodex review of 732b61f: adding MenuStateHandoff made it the THIRD latest-only\nsnapshot handoff, so the \"two latest-only snapshot handoffs\" / \"Both are type\naliases\" / \"the two handoffs above\" / Inspector+SaveStatus-only listings went\nstale. A complete multiline sweep widened every LIVE current-state spot to three\nand added MenuStateHandoff to the listings:\n- editor-egui-host/handoff.rs: module doc (two-\u003ethree, Both-\u003eAll three, + bullet).\n- editor-egui-host/lib.rs: EguiHost struct doc (two-\u003ethree + menu-state handoff);\n  the menu_command_handoff field doc (\"the two handoffs above\"-\u003ethree).\n- editor-shell/lifecycle/mod.rs: menu_command_handoff field doc (two-\u003ethree).\n- editor-shell/render_path.rs: init_render_state doc + comment (+MenuStateHandoff\n  clone), the \"clone its two handoffs\"-\u003ethree block (+ menu_state publish example).\n\nPreserved (historical, NOT stale): the Rule-of-Three notes about the 3 ORIGINAL\nhand-written copies (Inspector + SaveStatus + RenderHandoff) that motivated the\nshared generic (handoff.rs / render_input.rs / editor-state/handoff.rs) —\nMenuStateHandoff was always an alias, never one of those copies. Comments/docs\nonly; the .rs logic is byte-identical to the gate-passed 732b61f.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
