                       "message":  "PLAYMENU-DYNAMIC-ENABLE: widen the SNAPSHOT-set listings (parallel set)\n\nCodex round-3 on #302: adding MenuStateSnapshot made it the THIRD observation\naggregator, so the SNAPSHOT-set listings (the set parallel to the handoffs swept\nin rounds 1-2) went stale:\n- editor-state/lib.rs: the observation-aggregator listing\n  (InspectorSnapshot / SaveStatusSnapshot -\u003e + MenuStateSnapshot).\n- editor-state/handoff.rs: the dep-neutrality rationale listing (-\u003e + MenuState).\n- editor-egui-host/lib.rs: the rge-editor-state dependency-reasons listing\n  (Inspector/SaveStatus snapshots inside their handoffs -\u003e + MenuStateSnapshot\n  inside MenuStateHandoff).\n\nAn exhaustive WIDE-WINDOW co-mention sweep of BOTH sets (snapshot aggregators AND\nhandoffs) + the snapshot-method references now confirms every LIVE listing\nincludes the MenuState member. Correctly left: sibling-references (the new file\u0027s\n\"Like SaveStatus/Inspector\" doc), single mentions, the editor-ui widget listing\n(no menu widget exists), imports, and the historical Rule-of-Three notes.\nComment-only; logic byte-identical to 732b61f.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
