                       "message":  "PLAYMENU-DYNAMIC-ENABLE: widen the Handoff-alias listing in editor-state/lib.rs\n\nCodex round-4 on #302: editor-state/lib.rs:44 lists the type aliases over Handoff\n(editor-shell RenderHandoff + editor-egui-host InspectorHandoff / SaveStatusHandoff)\n— a THIRD listing locus, in editor-state, WRAPPED across lines, which my prior\nno-newline-bounded co-mention sweeps could not match. Added MenuStateHandoff (now\nalso a live alias over Handoff).\n\nA definitive newline-crossing ([\\s\\S]) co-mention sweep of the Handoff-alias set\nnow shows every LIVE \"aliases over Handoff\" / Inspector+SaveStatus listing includes\nthe MenuState member. Correctly left: the historical Rule-of-Three notes (handoff.rs\n+ render_input.rs) and the dated EDITOR-SAVE-STATUS-INDICATOR changelog block in\neditor-egui-host/lib.rs (\"owns BOTH\" / \"second latest-only handoff\" — accurate at\nthat dispatch\u0027s time; Codex confirmed this prose may remain). Comment-only; logic\nbyte-identical to 732b61f.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
